Use the nltk and gensim packages to transform the data to a corpus.¶

When transforming data to a corpus, we apply the following steps: terms of length less than 3 and the stop words, punctuation, numbers are removed; terms are then stemmed.

In [4]:
des = JSS_papers["description"]

# RegEx for words with length > 3
tokenizer = RegexpTokenizer(r'\b[a-zA-Z]{3,}\b') 
tokenized_des = [tokenizer.tokenize(s) for s in des]

# remove stop words
stop_words = stopwords.words('english')
tokenized_des = [[w for w in s if w not in stop_words] for s in tokenized_des]

# stemming the words
stemmer = SnowballStemmer("english")
tokenized_des = [[stemmer.stem(w) for w in s] for s in tokenized_des]

# create corpus
dct_des = corpora.Dictionary(tokenized_des) 
corpus_des = [dct_des.doc2bow(line) for line in tokenized_des]

Use TF-IDF (term frequency-inverse document frequency) to select the vocabulary.¶

Goal: filter terms with low frequences as well as those occurring in many documents. We only include terms whose TF-IDF values are at least 0.1, which is a bit more than the median and ensures that the very frequent terms are omitted.

In [5]:
tfidf_model = TfidfModel(corpus_des)  # fit tf-idf model

low_value_words = []
for bow in corpus_des:
    low_value_words += [id for id, value in tfidf_model[bow] if value < 0.1]
In [6]:
[dct_des.get(low_value_words[i]) for i in range(20)]

Fit an LDA model with 30 topics¶

The output is an LDA object, from which we obtain a term frequency vector (over all words) for each of the 30 topic, and other summaries from this topic model.

In [8]:
lda = LdaModel(corpus_des, num_topics=30, id2word=dct_des, passes=10, iterations=500)
In [9]:
# 5 most frequent terms for each top
# may also use lda.show_topics()
top_terms = []
for i in range(30):
    tmp_terms = lda.get_topic_terms(i, topn=5)
    top_terms.append([dct_des.get(tmp_terms[j][0]) for j in range(5)])

top_terms

Generate word clouds¶

In [10]:
# Wordcloud for individual topics
topic_id = [3, 5, 7, 11, 12, 26]

fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=2, ncols=3, figsize=(15, 10))
for i, idx in enumerate(topic_id):
    tmp_cloud = WordCloud(width=800, height=600, background_color="white")
    tmp_cloud.fit_words(dict(lda.show_topic(idx, 30)))
    axes[i // 3, i % 3].imshow(tmp_cloud)
    axes[i // 3, i % 3].axis('off')

fig.tight_layout()
